location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent: Extremely rare; of the millions of one variation or another of 336's made, only total of a little over 3000 were produced in 219 Zipper. First introduced in 1955 as a lever action varmint rifle these were not well received and few were sold. This one made in 1957 (P prefix), and discontinued in 1959. This one is in excellent fully original condition with no scratches, dings or imprecations except light evidence of having been carried, hunted and well cared for. There are no non factory holes and even the Marlin Bullseye in the butt stock is still in place as is the correct original (un chipped) Marlin Butt Plate. There is no pitting but light carry wear under receiver and mag tube is just now showing evidence of slightly browning. Slight flash burn at muzzle. Rear site removed and replace with a site blank and a nice Williams Peep (and hammer extension) go with the gun. There are some minor compression marks on left side of forend but no scratches or loss of finish and two faint scratches on left side of receiver.
